###############################################################################
# OBJECTIVE
###############################################################################
Ensure all glass/glow effects and animations meet WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility standards; verify keyboard navigation, screen reader support, and reduced motion support.

###############################################################################
# SCOPE
###############################################################################
Accessibility audit and fixes:
  1. Reduced motion support (prefers-reduced-motion)
  2. Color contrast (WCAG AA: 4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for large text/UI)
  3. Keyboard navigation
  4. Screen reader support (ARIA labels)
  5. Focus indicators

###############################################################################
# DELIVERABLES
###############################################################################
output:
  - Updated src/index.css with reduced-motion support
  - Updated components with ARIA labels (if needed)
  - Accessibility report: totem/instances/navitrack/sprints/44/S44-A11Y-REPORT.md

###############################################################################
# ACCESSIBILITY REQUIREMENTS
###############################################################################

1. Reduced Motion (prefers-reduced-motion):
   
   Current state:
   - glass-input: Has @media (prefers-reduced-motion) - GOOD
   - glass-glow::before: Has @media (prefers-reduced-motion) - GOOD
   - app-bg-pulse: NO reduced motion support - FIX NEEDED
   
   Required fixes:
   ```css
   @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
     .app-bg__layer--overlay {
       animation: none;
       background-color: rgba(var(--app-bg-overlay-light-rgb), var(--app-bg-pulse-opacity-high));
     }
     
     /* Verify other animations respect this setting */
     .glass-input,
     .glass-glow::before {
       animation: none; /* Already implemented, verify */
     }
   }
   ```
   
   Test: Enable prefers-reduced-motion in OS settings; verify animations stop

2. Color Contrast:
   
   Check contrast ratios:
   - Primary text on glass background
   - Muted text on glass background
   - Icon colors on glass background
   - Button text on glass-glow background
   
   Tools:
   - Chrome DevTools (Lighthouse)
   - WebAIM Contrast Checker
   - axe DevTools extension
   
   Minimum ratios:
   - Normal text (< 18pt): 4.5:1
   - Large text (≥ 18pt or 14pt bold): 3:1
   - UI components: 3:1
   
   Common issues:
   - text-muted-foreground on glass backgrounds
   - Icons on glass backgrounds
   - Placeholder text
   
   Fix: Adjust --muted-foreground or --glass-bg-opacity if needed

3. Keyboard Navigation:
   
   Verify all interactive elements are keyboard accessible:
   - [ ] Tab order is logical
   - [ ] All buttons reachable via Tab
   - [ ] Enter/Space activate buttons
   - [ ] Focus indicators visible on all elements
   - [ ] No keyboard traps
   
   Test:
   - Navigate entire app using only keyboard
   - Verify focus ring visible on all interactive elements
   - Ensure glass effects don't obscure focus indicators

4. Focus Indicators:
   
   Current state:
   - glass:focus-within has ring (good)
   - glass-input:focus-within has ring (good)
   
   Verify:
   - Focus ring visible on ALL interactive elements
   - Focus ring has sufficient contrast (3:1 minimum)
   - Focus ring not hidden by glass effects
   
   Fix if needed:
   - Increase focus ring size or contrast
   - Ensure z-index doesn't hide focus indicators

5. ARIA Labels:
   
   Verify ARIA labels on:
   - Icon-only buttons (Settings button, etc.)
   - Toggle switches
   - Status indicators (online/offline)
   
   Review all screens for:
   - [ ] Icon-only buttons have aria-label
   - [ ] Form inputs have associated labels
   - [ ] Status indicators have aria-live (if dynamic)
   - [ ] Loading states have aria-busy
   
   Current state (from code review):
   - Login screen: Eye icon toggle has aria-label - GOOD
   - Settings screen: Settings button has aria-label - GOOD
   - Objects screen: Verify all icon buttons

6. Screen Reader Support:
   
   Test with VoiceOver (macOS/iOS):
   - [ ] All interactive elements announced
   - [ ] Button labels clear
   - [ ] Form inputs have labels
   - [ ] Error messages announced
   - [ ] Loading states announced

